properties.otherAdvice:
From Monday 29 January to Monday 5 February, a large heavy vehicle movement will occur between Albury and Colongra. Motorists are being advised of traffic condition changes as the oversized vehicles travels along the Hume Hwy at a reduced speed. 

  • Thursday 1 February, the movement will take place between Gundagai and Goulburn. Alternating (stop/slow) traffic conditions will be in place for all Southbound traffic on the Sheahan Bridge for 10 minutes to allow the oversized vehicle to pass in one direction over the Murrumbidgee River at approximately 11pm.

Motorists are urged to slow down and to exercise caution when attempting to pass the oversized vehicle. Traffic controllers escorting the vehicle will direct motorists. For our safety, please follow all directions from these escort vehicles.

From Wednesday 31 Jan until Thursday 1 Feb, the road will be closed from 8am until 4pm each day.

Alternating (stop/slow) traffic conditions, with an escort vehicle, are in place between 8am and 6pm daily.
